On Fri, Jan 21, 2022 at 5:05 PM Andreas Tille  wrote:
>
> Hi,
>
> I've checked the build logs of muscle version 5.1[1] and noticed that
> for instance on arm64 the build fails with:
>
> g++ -Wdate-time -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 -DNDEBUG -pthread -g -O2 -ffile-prefix-map=/>=. -fstack-protector-strong -Wformat -Werror=format-security -O3 -fopenmp -ffast-math -c -o Linux/transaln.o transaln.cpp
> In file included from testlog.cpp:2:
> timing.h: In function ‘void cmd_testlog()’:
> timing.h:26:9: error: impossible constraint in ‘asm’
>    26 |         __asm__ __volatile__ ("rdtsc" : "=a" (lo), "=d" (hi));
>       |         ^~~~~~~

This assembly is for x86 based system. On arm64 you would want
something like this:

* https://stackoverflow.com/a/67968296/136285

Something is definitely wrong upstream.
